cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with 3D reconstruction of deformable objects, specifically hands, from a single image. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The approach involves training an autoencoder with intrinsic graph convolutions, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the system operates in real-time, which suggests that it may also involve multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
